597 !>@brief The subroutine 'p_adi' computes (ps, pk, pe, peln, pkz)
598 !! given (ptop, delp).
599 ✗ subroutine p_adi(km, ng, ifirst, ilast, jfirst, jlast, ptop, &
600 ✗ delp, pt, ps, pe, peln, pk, pkz, hydrostatic)
601 ! Given (ptop, delp) computes (ps, pk, pe, peln, pkz)
602 ! Input:
603 integer, intent(in):: km, ng
604 integer, intent(in):: ifirst, ilast !< Longitude strip
605 integer, intent(in):: jfirst, jlast !< Latitude strip
606 logical, intent(in):: hydrostatic
607 real, intent(in):: ptop
608 real, intent(in):: pt(ifirst-ng:ilast+ng,jfirst-ng:jlast+ng, km)
609 real, intent(in):: delp(ifirst-ng:ilast+ng,jfirst-ng:jlast+ng, km)
610 ! Output:
611 real, intent(out) :: ps(ifirst-ng:ilast+ng, jfirst-ng:jlast+ng)
612 real, intent(out) :: pk(ifirst:ilast, jfirst:jlast, km+1)
613 real, intent(out) :: pe(ifirst-1:ilast+1,km+1,jfirst-1:jlast+1) !< Ghosted Edge pressure
614 real, intent(out) :: peln(ifirst:ilast, km+1, jfirst:jlast) !< Edge pressure
615 real, intent(out) :: pkz(ifirst:ilast, jfirst:jlast, km)
616 ! Local
617 ✗ real pek
618 ✗ integer i, j, k
619
620 ✗ pek = ptop ** kappa
621 !$OMP parallel do default (none) &
622 !$OMP shared (ifirst,ilast,jfirst,jlast,km,ptop,pek,pe,pk, &
623 !$OMP ps,delp,peln,hydrostatic,pkz) &
624 !$OMP private (j, i, k)
625 ✗ do j=jfirst,jlast
626 ✗ do i=ifirst,ilast
627 ✗ pe(i,1,j) = ptop
628 ✗ pk(i,j,1) = pek
629 enddo
630
631 ✗ do k=2,km+1
632 ✗ do i=ifirst,ilast
633 ✗ pe(i,k,j) = pe(i,k-1,j) + delp(i,j,k-1)
634 ✗ peln(i,k,j) = log(pe(i,k,j))
635 ✗ pk(i,j,k) = exp( kappa*peln(i,k,j) )
636 enddo
637 enddo
638
639 ✗ do i=ifirst,ilast
640 ✗ ps(i,j) = pe(i,km+1,j)
641 enddo
642
643 ✗ if ( hydrostatic ) then
644 ✗ do k=1,km
645 ✗ do i=ifirst,ilast
646 ✗ pkz(i,j,k) = (pk(i,j,k+1)-pk(i,j,k))/(kappa*(peln(i,k+1,j)-peln(i,k,j)))
647 enddo
648 enddo
649 endif
650 enddo
651
652 ✗ end subroutine p_adi

863 !>@brief The subroutine 'atmosphere_restart' is an API to save restart information

1104 !>@brief The subroutine 'atmosphere_scalar_field_halo' is an API to return halo information
1105 !! of the current MPI_rank for an input scalar field.
1106 !>@detail Up to three point haloes can be returned by this API which includes special handling for
1107 !! the cubed-sphere tile corners. Output will be in (i,j,k) while input can be in (i,j,k) or
1108 !! horizontally-packed form (ix,k).
1109 ✗ subroutine atmosphere_scalar_field_halo (data, halo, isize, jsize, ksize, data_p)
1110 !--------------------------------------------------------------------
1111 ! data - output array to return the field with halo (i,j,k)
1112 ! optionally input for field already in (i,j,k) form
1113 ! sized to include the halo of the field (+ 2*halo)
1114 ! halo - size of the halo (must be less than 3)
1115 ! ied - horizontal resolution in i-dir with haloes
1116 ! jed - horizontal resolution in j-dir with haloes
1117 ! ksize - vertical resolution
1118 ! data_p - optional input field in packed format (ix,k)
1119 !--------------------------------------------------------------------
1120 !--- interface variables ---
1121 real(kind=kind_phys), dimension(1:isize,1:jsize,ksize), intent(inout) :: data !< output array to return the field with halo (i,j,k)
1122 !< optionally input for field already in (i,j,k) form
1123 !< sized to include the halo of the field (+ 2*halo)
1124 integer, intent(in) :: halo !< size of the halo (must be less than 3)
1125 integer, intent(in) :: isize !< horizontal resolution in i-dir with haloes
1126 integer, intent(in) :: jsize !< horizontal resolution in j-dir with haloes
1127 integer, intent(in) :: ksize !< vertical resolution
1128 real(kind=kind_phys), dimension(:,:), optional, intent(in) :: data_p !< optional input field in packed format (ix,k)
1129 !--- local variables ---
1130 ✗ integer :: i, j, k
1131 ✗ integer :: ic, jc
1132 character(len=44) :: modname = 'atmosphere_mod::atmosphere_scalar_field_halo'
1133 ✗ integer :: mpp_flags
1134
1135 !--- perform error checking
1136 ✗ if (halo .gt. 3) call mpp_error(FATAL, modname//' - halo.gt.3 requires extending the MPP domain to support')
1137 ✗ ic = isize - 2 * halo
1138 ✗ jc = jsize - 2 * halo
1139
1140 !--- if packed data is present, unpack it into the two-dimensional data array
1141 ✗ if (present(data_p)) then
1142 ✗ if (ic*jc .ne. size(data_p,1)) call mpp_error(FATAL, modname//' - incorrect sizes for incoming &
1143 ✗ &variables data and data_p')

1150 ✗ do i = 1, ic

1163 ✗ call mpp_error(FATAL, modname//' - unsupported halo size')
